The paper focuses on the design and testing of a hardware robot that can adapt its morphology to different environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of automatic self-reconfiguration also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The study also involves analyzing performance data, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) if image processing was involved.
